"# Project Overview\n\nAn AI-powered movie production platform (web + tablet responsive) to centralize pre-production workflows for film studios. The MVP enables production teams to create projects and manage scripts, cast & crew, shooting schedules, budgets, filming locations, assets, and basic post-production tasks. AI assistance (hosted LLM + deterministic modules) will provide script summarization, cost estimation, schedule optimization, conflict detection, and production reports. The product is single-tenant per studio and built with React frontend, Node.js backend, and Supabase (Postgres) for data and storage. Frontend deploys to Vercel; backend is managed (serverless or managed Node service).\n\n# Target Users\n\n- Producers (primary): create projects, approve budgets, view dashboards, request AI reports  \n- Production Managers / 1st AD: create and optimize shooting schedules, resolve conflicts, assign crew  \n- Directors: review scripts, mark scenes, provide creative notes  \n- Assistant Directors: refine and enforce schedules, manage on-set resources  \n- Finance teams: create / approve budgets, track costs and payments  \n- Editors and Post-production leads: manage post tasks and assets (basic in MVP)  \n- Crew members: view assigned call sheets/schedules, comment, and acknowledge tasks  \n- Admins / Studio IT: manage users, permissions, studio settings, data exports\n\n# Functional Requirements\n\nCore MVP functionality (prioritized):\n\n1. Project lifecycle\n   - Create/manage project metadata (title, studio, production dates, status)\n   - Associate scripts, schedules, budgets, locations, assets, tasks, and team members with a project\n\n2. Script management (MVP)\n   - Upload scripts (PDF, Fountain/TXT)\n   - Parse script into scenes/sluglines with metadata (scene number, INT/EXT, day/night, page count)\n   - Version history for script uploads\n   - AI script summarization: generate short (2–3 sentence) and extended (1 paragraph) summaries\n   - Script annotations/comments and basic access controls\n\n3. People (cast & crew) management\n   - Create and import people (name, role, rate, availability window, contact info)\n   - Role-based assignments (actor/department/position)\n   - Availability calendar integration (optional, MVP deferred to basic manual availability)\n\n4. Shooting schedules\n   - Build day-by-day shooting schedule (scenes, location, cast & crew required, estimated duration)\n   - Drag-and-drop reordering UI (frontend)\n   - AI schedule optimization: propose schedule permutations to minimize location moves, cast idle time, and estimated cost\n   - Conflict detection (AI + deterministic): overlapping person assignments, overbooked locations, resource conflicts\n   - Call sheet generation (PDF export) from schedule\n\n5. Budgeting & cost tracking\n   - Create budget line items (cast fees, crew, equipment, locations, travel, per-diem)\n   - Track committed vs estimated vs actual spend\n   - AI cost estimation: given script/scene metadata and crew/cast rates, produce an estimated budget summary and per-day estimates\n\n6. Filming locations\n   - Location records with address, primary contact, booking constraints, capacity, booking cost estimates\n   - Map view (integrated with Maps API) and per-location metadata\n\n7. Production assets & basic post tasks\n   - Upload and tag assets (storyboards, shot lists, equipment specs) with version history\n   - Create basic post-production tasks (editor assignments, deliverable list)\n   - Asset storage and retrieval (preview, metadata)\n\n8. Collaboration & workflows\n   - Comments on scripts, schedules, budgets, assets\n   - Approvals workflow: request → approve/reject with audit trail (MVP: single-step approvals per object)\n   - In-app notifications and email notifications for mentions, approvals, schedule changes\n   - Shared timelines and dashboards with role-filtered views\n\n9. Dashboards & analytics\n   - Project overview dashboard (status, budget summary, upcoming shoot days)\n   - AI-generated production report (summary + key risks/opportunities)\n\n10. User and permission management\n    - Email/password authentication (Supabase Auth)\n    - Role-based access control (role matrix described in Security Requirements)\n    - Single-tenant isolation per studio (org-scoped data)\n\nAI-specific behavior:\n- Hosted LLM endpoints used for summarization, conflict explanation text, and report generation.\n- Deterministic business logic + small ML/regression/heuristic modules (hosted within backend or worker) used for cost estimation and schedule optimization; optionally call out to an optimization microservice for CP-SAT if required.\n\n# Non-functional Requirements\n\n- Availability: Target 99.9% uptime for core web UI and API.\n- Scalability: MVP should support an initial scale of 1,000 active users across 50 studio tenants, with architecture to scale horizontally.\n- Performance:\n  - Standard API requests: median latency < 200–300 ms under nominal load\n  - AI endpoints: variable; typical response < 3–8 seconds (depends on LLM provider)\n  - Real-time updates (schedules/comments): < 2s propagation in-session\n- Concurrency: Support multiple users editing/viewing the same schedule with optimistic concurrency controls and conflict notifications.\n- Durability & backups: daily logical backups of Postgres; snapshots of storage; 30–90 day retention policy configurable per studio.\n- Observability: request logging, metrics (request rate, errors, latencies), tracing for AI and schedule optimization jobs, alerts for high error rates and resource exhaustion.\n- Data residency: configurable per contract (default: deploy in US region). Store PII per legal and privacy requirements.\n- Compliance: prepare to support GDPR/CCPA requests, maintain audit logs for access to sensitive assets.\n- Resilience: replayable background job queue for long-running jobs (AI calls, schedule optimization).\n\n# Recommended Technology Stack\n\nFrontend\n- React + TypeScript\n- UI kit: Chakra UI / Tailwind CSS (responsive + accessibility)\n- State management: React Query (server state) + local state via Context\n- Build & deploy: Vercel\n\nBackend\n- Node.js (TypeScript) serverless API (Vercel Serverless Functions or managed Node on Render/Heroku)\n- Framework: Fastify / Express (lightweight)\n- Background workers: Node.js workers or small Python worker for optimization jobs (deployed as separate service)\n- Task queue: Managed queue (e.g., Supabase Realtime + Background Functions / Redis + BullMQ) or cloud task service\n\nDatabase & Storage\n- Supabase (Postgres) for relational data, Row-Level Security (RLS), Auth\n- Supabase Storage for assets (or S3 via Supabase if required)\n- Realtime: Supabase Realtime or Pusher for WebSocket updates\n\nAI & ML\n- Hosted LLM provider (OpenAI, Anthropic, or other provider) for summarization and free-text insights\n- Deterministic cost model: server-side rule-based calculator with configurable rate tables\n- Schedule optimization: staged approach:\n  1. Heuristics & greedy algorithms implemented in Node\n  2. If higher-quality results needed: CP-SAT solver microservice (Python + OR-Tools) behind an API\n\nIntegrations\n- Email: SendGrid or Postmark\n- Calendar (MVP optional): Google Calendar / Microsoft Graph (OAuth)\n- Maps: Google Maps or Mapbox (geocoding & map UI)\n- Optional: Payment processor or accounting integration (deferred to later)\n\nCI/CD & DevOps\n- GitHub Actions for CI (linting, tests, build)\n- Infrastructure as code: Terraform (if customizing cloud infra)\n- Monitoring: Sentry for errors, Prometheus/Grafana or hosted metrics via provider\n\n# System Architecture\n\nComponents and flow:\n1. Frontend (React, Vercel)\n   - UI + client-side caching, talks to Backend via REST/GraphQL and subscribes to Realtime updates.\n2. Backend API (Node.js)\n   - Auth (Supabase Auth via JWT)\n   - CRUD APIs for projects, scripts, people, schedules, budgets, assets, tasks\n   - AI gateway endpoints that orchestrate calls to LLM provider and deterministic modules\n   - Background job enqueuer for heavy tasks (script parsing, schedule optimization, batch reports)\n3. Worker(s)\n   - Process long-running jobs (script parsing, optimization, large exports)\n   - Connect to optimization microservice when needed\n4. Database & Storage (Supabase)\n   - Postgres store with RLS and audit tables\n   - Storage buckets for assets with metadata in DB\n   - Realtime service for collaboration (pub/sub)\n5. AI Provider\n   - Hosted LLM for summarization & textual insights\n   - Backend enforces prompt templates, rate limits, and caches AI responses\n6. Notification Service\n   - Email provider for email notifications\n   - In-app notification persisted in DB and delivered via Realtime\n7. External integrations\n   - Calendar, Maps, and optional third-party services via secured OAuth flows\n8. Observability & Ops\n   - Logging, tracing, metrics ingestors and dashboards; alerting on SLO violations\n\nSecurity & tenancy:\n- Single-tenant per studio: data isolation via organization scoping, separate storage buckets and strict RLS policies. Admin UI to manage org settings.\n\n# Database Requirements\n\nPrimary entities (with key fields; MVP schema notes):\n\n- Organization (studio)\n  - id, name, plan, region, created_at, settings\n\n- User\n  - id, org_id, name, email, hashed_auth (managed by Supabase), role(s), last_active, MFA_enabled\n\n- Project\n  - id, org_id, title, description, status(enum), start_date, end_date, created_by, version_token, created_at\n\n- Script\n  - id, project_id, uploaded_by, file_url, file_type, parsed_json (scenes[]), version_number, change_notes, uploaded_at, ai_summary_short, ai_summary_long\n\n- Scene (derived via parsing)\n  - id, script_id, scene_number, slugline, interior_exterior, day_night, page_estimate, estimated_minutes\n\n- Person\n  - id, org_id, name, role (actor/crew), rate_type (daily/hour), rate_amount, contact, availability_windows[], notes\n\n- Location\n  - id, org_id, name, address, latlng, capacity, booking_cost_estimate, booking_constraints\n\n- Schedule / ShootDay\n  - id, project_id, date, scenes[], location_id, call_time, wrap_time, notes, status\n\n- ScheduleAssignment (join)\n  - id, schedule_id, person_id, role, time_on_set_estimate\n\n- Budget & BudgetItem\n  - id, project_id, category, description, estimated_amount, committed_amount, actual_amount, vendor, approval_status\n\n- Asset\n  - id, project_id, storage_path, file_type, metadata (thumbnail, pages), uploaded_by, versions[], protected_flag\n\n- Comment\n  - id, entity_type, entity_id, author_id, body, created_at, resolved_flag\n\n- Approval\n  - id, entity_type, entity_id, requested_by, status, approver_ids, logs\n\n- AuditLog\n  - id, org_id, user_id, action_type, entity_ref, payload, timestamp\n\n- Notification\n  - id, user_id, org_id, type, payload, delivered, read_at\n\nRequirements:\n- Version history for scripts and assets (store diffs or full versions; keep last N versions, configurable).\n- Soft delete flag + archival policy for major objects.\n- Row-Level Security policies: users can only access rows where org_id = user's org_id and role checks.\n- Indexing: project_id, org_id, user_id, created_at; full-text index on scripts/notes for search.\n- File uploads: support PDF, TXT, image, video placeholders. Per-file size limit (e.g., 200MB for MVP; large VFX files handled later via external VFX storage).\n- Data retention: default retention 365 days for project data unless archived; backups daily.\n\n# External Integrations\n\nMVP: prioritized integrations\n- Email: SendGrid / Postmark (MVP) — transactional notifications and invites\n- Maps: Google Maps or Mapbox (MVP) — map UI, geocoding for locations\n- Calendar (MVP optional): Google Calendar / Microsoft Outlook via OAuth — sync call sheets/events\n- Auth: Supabase Auth (email/password), with option to extend to SSO (SAML/OIDC) later\n\nDeferred / future integrations\n- Accounting / Payroll systems (QuickBooks, Xero)\n- VFX asset storage (Perforce, ShotGrid)\n- Payment processors (Stripe) for deposits/payments\n- Weather APIs for shoot day risk scoring\n\nIntegration details\n- Use OAuth 2.0 for calendar & map APIs where needed\n- Provide per-org integration settings with token storage in encrypted secrets store (via Supabase secrets or managed backend)\n- Provide opt-in UI for enabling calendar sync for users\n\n# Security Requirements\n\nAuthentication & Access Control\n- Use Supabase Auth (email/password) as MVP. Enforce email verification.\n- Support MFA as optional feature (recommend TOTP).\n- Authorization: Role-Based Access Control (RBAC) + org-scoped Row-Level Security.\n  - Roles: Admin, Producer, Director, 1st AD, Finance, Editor, Crew\n  - Permissions matrix defined and enforced in APIs and DB policies.\n\nData protection\n- TLS everywhere (HTTPS) for transport.\n- Encryption at rest using provider defaults (Supabase / underlying cloud).\n- Secure storage of API keys and OAuth tokens in environment variables / secrets manager.\n- Audit logs for read/write access to sensitive resources (scripts, budgets, people).\n- Soft delete plus an immutable audit trail for approvals/financial changes.\n- Optional script watermarking for exported PDFs (to protect IP).\n\nAI safety & governance\n- Prompt templates stored centrally, with input sanitization and output caching.\n- LLM outputs tagged with provenance metadata (prompt used, model id, timestamp).\n- Implement rate limiting, output length limits, and safety filters for generated text (avoid hallucination risk by bounding claims).\n- Provide user UI to flag/feedback incorrect AI outputs; log feedback for model improvement.\n\nOperational security\n- Least privilege IAM for cloud resources.\n- Regular dependency scanning and SCA tooling in CI.\n- Periodic backups and a documented incident response runbook.\n- Penetration testing before public release.\n\nPrivacy & Compliance\n- Store minimal PII required. Provide data export and deletion workflows for GDPR/CCPA compliance.\n- Per-org data residency options where required (contracted).\n\n# API Requirements\n\nGeneral\n- RESTful JSON API (versioned: /api/v1/)\n- Auth via JWT (Supabase-issued). All endpoints require org_id scoping.\n- Rate limiting per user/org (configurable)\n- Provide OpenAPI (Swagger) specification as deliverable.\n\nKey endpoints (representative; full list required in API spec deliverable)\n- Auth & User\n  - POST /auth/signup, POST /auth/login, POST /auth/refresh, GET /users/me\n- Organization\n  - GET /orgs/:orgId, PUT /orgs/:orgId/settings\n- Projects\n  - POST /orgs/:orgId/projects\n  - GET /orgs/:orgId/projects/:projectId\n  - PATCH /orgs/:orgId/projects/:projectId\n- Scripts\n  - POST /orgs/:orgId/projects/:projectId/scripts (file upload + parse job)\n  - GET /orgs/:orgId/projects/:projectId/scripts/:scriptId\n  - POST /orgs/:orgId/projects/:projectId/scripts/:scriptId/ai-summarize\n  - GET /orgs/:orgId/projects/:projectId/scripts/:scriptId/versions\n- People\n  - CRUD /orgs/:orgId/people\n- Schedules\n  - CRUD /orgs/:orgId/projects/:projectId/schedules\n  - POST /orgs/:orgId/projects/:projectId/schedules/optimize (background job)\n  - GET /orgs/:orgId/projects/:projectId/schedules/:id/conflicts\n- Budgets\n  - CRUD /orgs/:orgId/projects/:projectId/budgets and /items\n  - POST /orgs/:orgId/projects/:projectId/budgets/estimate (AI or deterministic)\n- Assets\n  - POST /orgs/:orgId/projects/:projectId/assets (upload)\n  - GET /orgs/:orgId/projects/:projectId/assets/:id/preview\n- Comments & Approvals\n  - POST /comments, GET /entity/:id/comments\n  - POST /approvals, PATCH /approvals/:id\n- Notifications\n  - GET /users/:id/notifications, POST /notifications/mark-read\n- AI & Reports\n  - POST /ai/summarize-script {script_id}\n  - POST /ai/estimate-cost {project_id, parameters}\n  - POST /ai/optimize-schedule {project_id, constraints}\n  - POST /ai/detect-conflicts {schedule_id}\n  - POST /ai/generate-report {project_id, scope}\n- Realtime\n  - WebSocket subscription endpoints or use Supabase Realtime channels for: schedules, comments, notifications\n\nAPI response patterns\n- Use standard HTTP status codes. Provide consistent error codes and structured error body {code, message, details}.\n- All AI responses include metadata: model_used, prompt_id, generated_at, confidence_hint (if available), cached boolean.\n\n# Deployment\n\nEnvironment\n- Staging and Production environments with separate Supabase instances or separate schemas/buckets per org (configurable).\n- Frontend: Vercel with auto-deploy from main branch & preview deployments for PRs\n- Backend: Vercel serverless functions or managed Node service (Render/Heroku) with autoscale\n- Workers: deployed as separate managed services or containers (e.g., Render, Railway, or serverless background functions)\n\nCI/CD\n- GitHub Actions pipeline:\n  - Pre-merge: lint, typecheck, unit tests\n  - Post-merge: build, integration tests, deploy to staging\n  - Manual promotion to production with smoke tests\n\nSecrets\n- Store AI keys, email provider keys, OAuth client secrets in environment secrets (Vercel + secrets manager)\n- Rotate keys periodically and provide mechanism to revoke per-org tokens\n\nMonitoring & Alerts\n- Integrate Sentry for runtime errors\n- Metrics (Prometheus/Grafana or hosted equivalent)\n- Uptime monitoring and incident notifications via PagerDuty/Slack\n\nBackups & Recovery\n- Daily DB logical backup and periodic snapshots\n- Storage backups for assets\n- Test restore monthly; maintain RTO/RPO targets in runbook\n\n# Testing Strategy\n\nTest types and coverage:\n- Unit tests: business logic, parsers, cost calculator, access control (Node.js, Jest)\n- Integration tests: API endpoints, DB migrations, RLS policies\n- End-to-end tests: Cypress for core user flows (project creation, script upload & parse, schedule create & optimize, approval)\n- Contract tests: OpenAPI validation and endpoint contract tests\n- AI evaluation tests:\n  - Prompt-response validation with synthetic scripts and expected summaries\n  - Regression checks for hallucination/quality with sample dataset\n- Performance & load testing:\n  - Load test API (k6 or Artillery) simulating up to initial target concurrency\n  - Stress test background jobs (optimizers, LLM calls)\n- Security testing:\n  - Static analysis (Snyk), dependency scanning\n  - Dynamic scanners and pen testing before production release\n- Accessibility (a11y) testing: automated (axe) + manual spot checks (WCAG AA target)\n\nData & test fixtures\n- Provide synthetic dataset: sample scripts, sample budgets, people roster, location list to seed staging for tests and QA.\n\n# Acceptance Criteria\n\nMVP acceptance criteria (measurable):\n\n1. Project creation\n   - Create a project with required metadata; visible in dashboard. (Functional test pass)\n\n2. Script upload & summarization\n   - Upload a script PDF (<= 20MB). Backend parses into scenes within 2 minutes and stores parsed scenes.\n   - AI returns short and long summary within expected latency (<= 15s). Summaries present in UI.\n\n3. People management\n   - Create/import 10 people and assign them to scenes; availability editable.\n\n4. Schedule creation and optimization\n   - Create a 5-day schedule with scene assignments.\n   - Schedule optimization endpoint returns a viable alternative schedule respecting availability and reducing location moves by > 10% in test dataset (heuristic acceptance).\n   - Conflict detection identifies overlapping person assignments and reports them.\n\n5. Budgeting and cost estimation\n   - Create budget with line items; AI cost estimation generates per-day estimate and total, with configurable rate inputs.\n   - Budget change history recorded and visible.\n\n6. Assets and versioning\n   - Upload assets (images/PDFs), create a new asset version, and retrieve older versions.\n\n7. Collaboration & workflow\n   - Post comments on a schedule item; notifications delivered in-app and emailed to mentioned users.\n   - Approval flow: request → approve triggers audit log entry.\n\n8. Security & multi-tenant isolation\n   - Users from one org cannot access data from another (RLS enforcement tests pass).\n\n9. Reliability & performance\n   - API basic endpoints median latency < 300ms on staging load tests.\n   - AI endpoints succeed for test prompts within configured retries.\n\n10. Observability & monitoring\n   - Errors captured in Sentry and critical metrics alerting configured.\n\n# Deliverables\n\n- Product artifacts\n  - Full engineering specification (this document + supplemental ERD)\n  - Role & permission matrix\n  - OpenAPI (Swagger) spec for all endpoints\n  - Prompt templates and AI governance notes\n  - UI wireframes for core screens (project dashboard, script viewer, schedule editor, budget editor, approvals)\n\n- Code & infra\n  - Frontend: React (TS) app, components, pages, and build config\n  - Backend: Node.js (TS) API with documented routes & auth\n  - Worker: background worker service for parsing & optimization\n  - Deployment config: GitHub Actions workflows, Vercel setup docs, Terraform (if used)\n  - Supabase schema migrations and seed scripts for sample data\n\n- Testing & QA\n  - Unit, integration, and E2E test suites with CI integration\n  - Load test scripts and results\n  - Security scan and remediation log\n\n- Ops & runbooks\n  - Monitoring dashboards and alerting rules\n  - Backup & restore playbook\n  - Incident response runbook for P1/P2 incidents\n\n- Sample data\n  - Synthetic scripts, roster, schedules, and budgets for AI validation and QA\n\n- Handover docs\n  - Developer onboarding README, environment setup, API usage examples, and maintenance notes\n\nNotes on phased scope and risk mitigation\n- MVP focuses on pre-production. Defer deep post-production and heavy VFX asset workflows to later phases.\n- AI risk: LLM outputs may hallucinate budget or scheduling claims. Mitigate with conservative UI phrasing, provenance metadata, and human-in-the-loop approval for AI-generated budgets/schedules.\n- Optimization risk: For early MVP use heuristics; if solver quality is insufficient, introduce a CP-SAT microservice in a follow-up sprint.\n\nThis specification gives a concrete, implementable foundation for an AI-assisted movie production MVP. Next steps: produce the ERD + OpenAPI spec and prioritized sprint plan (3–4 sprints) for implementation."